    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Christian religious monument in the form of a column and dedicated to the Virgin Mary, erected as a gesture of public faith, as a plague column, or for another purpose. Common in Catholic countries of Europe, especially in the 17th and 18th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
